    {
      "text": "Ghouls 'n Ghosts, known as Dai Makaimura in Japan, is a 1988 platform game developed and published by Capcom for arcades. It is the sequel to 1985's Ghosts 'n Goblins, and the second game in the Ghosts 'n Goblins series.\nIt was a commercial success, becoming the eighth highest-grossing arcade game of 1989 in Japan. It was also critically acclaimed, with the Sega Genesis version winning four awards from Electronic Gaming Monthly in 1989, including Best Game of the Year.",
